  "text": "Component or characteristic Liquid medium 10.0 g/l glucose, 2.5 g/l (NH4)2SO4, 0.8 g/l MnSO4, 1.0 g/l KH2PO4, 0.8 g/l MgSO4, 0.5 g/l CaCl2, and 0.7% trace element solution containing 0.5 g/l glycine, 0.1 g/l FeSO4·7H2O, 0.1 g/l ZnSO4, 10 mg/l CuSO4·5H2O, 10 mg/l H2BO3 and 10 mg/l Na2MoO2·2H2O Synthetic wastewater 2.0 g/l glucose, 0.5 g/l phenol, 2.0 g/l NH4Cl, 2.0 g/l KH2PO4, 0.8 g/l MgSO4·7 H2O, 0.5 mg/l MnSO4 and 0.1 g/l CaCl2 Coking wastewater COD: 2031 mg/l; phenol: 700 mg/l; suspended solids: 660 mg/l; pH: 7.5-8.2 Meat-peptone agar medium 3.0 g/l beef extract, 10 g/l peptone, 5.0 g/l NaCl and 20 g/l agar Martin agar medium 10 g/l glucose, 5.0 g/l peptone, 1.0 g/l KH2PO4, 0.5 g/l MgSO4·7H2O and 20 g/l agar TCCTGGCTCAG-3 ) and 533R (5 -TTACCGCGGCTGCTGGCAC-3 ) for bacteria and 3NDF (5 -GGCAAGTCTGGTGCCAG-3 ) and V4euk R2 (5 -ACGGTATCT(AG)ATC(AG)TCTTCG-3 ) for eukaryotic cells were used for PCR quantification [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The PCR was run at 95 • C for 30 s, 40 cycles of denaturing (5 s at 94 • C), annealing (34 s at 63 • C for bacteria; 60 • C for fungi), and a melting curve analysis from 60 • C to 95 • C, with the plate being read every 0.5 • C. The qRT-PCR assay was conducted in a volume of 25 l on an ABI 7500Q-PCR machine (USA) using an SYBR green detection system and an SYBR premix EX Taq TM kit (Takara, China). Both agarose gel electrophoresis and melting curve analysis were conducted to confirm the specificity of the amplified products. Three independent PCR assays were performed on each of the three replicate DNA samples.",
